-- Indian shares mark record closing high on Euro zone stimulus talk
-- By Abhishek Vishnoi
-- Wed Aug 27, 2014 06:03AM EDT
-- None



MUMBAI, Aug 27 (Reuters) - Indian shares rose on Wednesday to a record closing high as expectations of further monetary stimulus in the Euro zone raised hopes of continued foreign inflows, lifting blue-chips such as ICICI Bank Ltd <ICBK.NS>.

Tata Motors <TAMO.NS> provisionally ended 2.2 percent higher while ICICI Bank rose 2.5 percent.